The paper focuses on the experimental analysis of design elements of multiobjective evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in optimization problems. The paper discusses the importance of different design elements, such as parent selection and weight vectors, in the performance of these algorithms. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and robotics (cs.RO).
